summary: The TOBACCO INSTITUTE is located in Raleigh, North Carolina, United States. The building was built in the 1960s and 1970s. It is currently home to the Toragco Institute of Architects and Engineers, which was founded in 1968. Its name translates to "The Torage Centre for Architecture and Design"
